a}}</ref>{{·}}[[Georg Brandes|Brandes]]{{·}}[[Martin Buber|Buber]]{{·}}[[Kenneth Burke|Burke]]{{·}}[[Joseph Campbell|Campbell]]{{·}}[[Albert Camus|Camus]]{{·}}[[Ivan Cankar|Cankar]]{{·}}[[Emil Cioran|Cioran]]{{·}}[[Gilles Deleuze|Deleuze]]{{·}}[[Gabriele D'Annunzio|D'Annunzio]]<ref>{{cite book |last=Aschheim |first=Steven E |title=The Nietzsche legacy in Germany, 1890–1990 |year=1992 |publisher=University of California Press |page=56}}</ref>{{·}}[[Pierre Drieu La Rochelle|Drieu]]<ref>{{cite journal |last=Hawkins |first=Mike |title=The foundations of fascism: The world views of Drieu la Rochelle |journal=Journal of Political Ideologies |year=2000 |volume=5 |issue=3 |pages=321–41}}</ref>{{·}}[[Alfred Döblin|Döblin]]{{·}}[[Lawrence Durrell|Durrell]]<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.ualberta.ca/~gifford/textsvictoria.htm |place=[[CAnada|CA]] |publisher=University of Alberta |title=Reevaluating Postcolonial Theory in Lawrence Durrell's Alexandria Quartet}}</ref>{{·}}[[Alain de Benoist|de Benoist]]{{·}}[[Jacques Derrida|Derrida]]{{·}}[[D. H. Lawrence]]<ref>{{cite book |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=l_tSP0DZzK0C&pg=PA210&dq=d.h.+lawrence+nietzsche&hl=en&sa=X&ei=ss2iT_CjL8ftOeHixN8G&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=d.h.%20lawrence%20nietzsche&f=false |title= D.H. Lawrence: The Early Years, 1885-1912 |first=Worthen |last=John}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=64flYHlI9cQC&pg=PA73&dq=d.h.+lawrence+nietzsche&hl=en&sa=X&ei=ss2iT_CjL8ftOeHixN8G&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=d.h.%20lawrence%20nietzsche&f=false |title= The Visionary D. H. Lawrence: Beyond Philosophy and Art |first=Montgomery |last=Robert}}</ref>{{·}}[[Julius Evola|Evola]]{{·}}[[Michel Foucault|Foucault]]{{·}}[[Sigmund Freud|Freud]]{{·}}[[Emma Goldman|Goldman]]{{·}}[[George Grant (philosopher)|Grant]]{{·}}[[Otto Gross|Gross]]{{·}}[[André Gide|Gide]]<ref>{{cite book |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=mZGxs0PCwzEC&pg=PA164&lpg=PA164&dq=Andr%C3%A9+Gide+Nietzsche&source=bl&ots=hrOYmXJZMg&sig=6zmgn7