aufmann|1974|pp=214–15}}{{·}}[[Miroslav Krleža|Krleža]]<ref>{{cite book |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=qYfH1tOwsHcC&pg=PA304&lpg=PA304&dq=Krleza+Nietzsche&source=bl&ots=j2VZ2f1mm6&sig=RILoQVWCI7sAOk1LdaLktTuF8Bg&hl=en&sa=X&ei=E5ZAT6GMLIrXsgaDttHmBA&ved=0CFUQ6AEwCA#v=onepage&q=Krleza%20Nietzsche&f=false |title= The Columbia encyclopedia of modern drama |volume=1}} Also, one of Krleža's first works was called ''Zarathustra and young man''.</ref>{{·}}[[Károly Kerényi|Kerényi]]{{·}}[[Milan Kundera|Kundera]]{{·}}[[Nikos Kazantzakis|Kazantzakis]]{{·}}[[Wyndham Lewis|Lewis]]<ref>{{cite book |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=COWpq79R5bsC&pg=PA109&dq=Wyndham+Lewis+Nietzsche&hl=en&sa=X&ei=81NBT46XKsnQsgbj8JHTBA&ved=0CE8Q6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=Wyndham%20Lewis%20Nietzsche&f=false |title=Morality and the literary imagination}}</ref>{{·}}[[Henri Lefebvre|Lefebvre]]{{·}}[[Jack London|London]]<ref>{{citation |url=http://london.sonoma.edu/Essays/philosophy.html |title=The Philosophy of Jack London |publisher=Sonoma}}.</ref>{{·}}[[Oscar Levy|Levy]]{{·}}[[Väinö Linna|Linna]]{{·}}[[H.P. Lovecraft|Lovecraft]]{{·}}[[Fritz Lang|Lang]]{{·}}[[Lu Xun]]<ref>{{cite book |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=8m7ENeccqaQC&pg=PA197&dq=Lu+Xun+Nietzsche&hl=en&sa=X&ei=m41AT_euBNDGswb5zOHVBA&ved=0CD0Q6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=Lu%20Xun%20Nietzsche&f=false |title=Lu Xun and evolution |first=James Reeve |last=Pusey}}</ref>{{·}}[[Anthony Ludovici|Ludovici]]{{·}}[[Dmitry Merezhkovsky|Merezhkovsky]]{{·}}[[Thomas Mann|Mann]]{{·}}[[H.L. Mencken|Mencken]]{{·}}[[Gustav Mahler|Mahler]]<ref>{{cite book |url=http://www.sydneysymphony.com/learn_and_explore/audio_features/mahler_and_nietzsche/ |title=MahlerandNietzsche}}</ref>{{·}}[[Thierry Maulnier|Maulnier]]<ref>{{cite book |last=Witt |first=Mary Ann Frese |title=The search for modern tragedy: aesthetic fascism in Italy and France |year=2001 |publisher=Cornell University Press |pages=139–41}}</ref>{{·}}[[Vladimir Mayakovski|Mayakovski]]<ref>{{cite book |url=http: